speaker: ['Ross Geller']

transcript: Hey!

transcript: I'm sorry I'm late, did I miss anything?

transcript: Joey stuffing 15 Oreos in his mouth.

transcript: Where were you?

transcript: Oh, on a date. Yeah, I met this girl on the train going to a museum upstate.

transcript: Oh, which museum?

transcript: No, answer his.

transcript: Okay, it was just me and her at the back of the train, and I sat near the door, so she'd have to pass by me if she wanted to switch cars. She was totally at my mercy.

transcript: Were you so late because you were burring this woman?

transcript: No, I'm getting back down 'cause she lives in Poughkeepsie. She seems really great, but she's like totally great, but she lives two and a half hours away.

transcript: How can she be great if she's from Poughkeepsie? That joke would've killed in Albany.

transcript: Done! I did it! Heh, who's stupid now?

speaker: ['Chandler Bing']
transcript: I say, Drew! Are you seeing anybody right now? Og-ee-op, I'm not asking for me, I'm... I mean... No, I'm-I'm not gay, I'm not asking you out. I'm not-I'm not-I'm not gay!

transcript: I didn't think you were gay. I do now.

speaker: ['Chandler Bing']
transcript: See my friend-my friend, Rachel, she wants to be set up.

speaker: ['Drew']
transcript: Ahh, I just got out of a big relationship, I'm not looking for any thing serious.

speaker: ['Chandler Bing']
transcript: Oh, y'know what, that might be okay even if it was just kind of a fling, that might be all right with Rachel.

speaker: ['Mike']
transcript: Whoa-whoa-whoa-whoa! Is this, hot Rachel, that you took to the Christmas party, Rachel?

speaker: ['Chandler Bing']
transcript: Oh, by the way, that is her full name.

speaker: ['Mike']
transcript: Oh wow! I'm free for her!

speaker: ['Drew']
transcript: Oh, wait a second! I didn't say I wasn't free!

speaker: ['Mike']
transcript: Hey, Chandler, why don't we talk this over at the Ranger game tomorrow?

speaker: ['Drew']
transcript: Hold on, y'know I just got a box of Cubans, maybe I bring them by your office around uh, five?

transcript: Oh well, that's uh, a little later than I uh, generally care to stay, but sure!

speaker: ['Mike']
transcript: Maybe, before the game we could enjoy some eight year old some small batch Basel Hadens.

speaker: ['Chandler Bing']
transcript: Well, I don't really know what that is, but let's!!

speaker: ['Ross Geller']
transcript: Oh, wow! I should get going. I-I got a date tonight.

transcript: Oh yeah! With who?

speaker: ['Ross Geller']
transcript: You know that girl I told you about who lives up in Poughkeepsie?

speaker: ['Chandler Bing']
transcript: Yeah.

speaker: ['Ross Geller']
transcript: Not her. Yeah, this is someone else I meet, and I-I can't decide between the two of them. Y'know the one from Poughkeepsie, even though she's a two hour train ride away, is really pretty, really smart, and-and a lot of fun. But this other girl, well, she lives right uptown. Y'know she's, well she's-she's just as pretty, I guess she's smart, she's not fun.

speaker: ['Phoebe Buffay']
transcript: If she's no fun, why do you want to date her at all?

speaker: ['Ross Geller']
transcript: Well, I-I want to give her another chance, y'know? She lives so close. And, at the end of the date, the other time, she-she said something that was-if she was kidding was very funny. On the other hand, if she wasn't kidding, she's not fun, she's stupid, and kind of a racist.

transcript: Hey!

transcript: Hey!

transcript: Hey! Ooh, how was your first day working at the restaurant?

transcript: Hey.

transcript: What are you doing?!

transcript: Chandler!! You have the best taste in men!

transcript: Patrick and I had such a great time last night! I mean I think this could maybe turn into something serious.

transcript: You told this guy that I was looking for a fling?! You don't tell the guy that!

transcript: Hey, Joey, could you pass the cheese?

transcript: Hey, dragon! Here's your tips from Monday and Tuesday.

transcript: There's like-there's like 300 bucks in this one!

transcript: Yeah, people get pretty generous around the holidays. And it never hurts to wear tight trousers.

speaker: ['Monica Geller']
transcript: Okay. Could the waiters gather around to hear tonight's specials? Okay, first there is a Chilean Sea Bass prepared with a Mango relish on a bag-Why is nobody writing these down?

transcript: Because we can remember them.

transcript: Because your all gonna make up fake specials and make me cook them like you did the other night?

transcript: Well, sure, that too.

transcript: Okay, forget the specials for a minute. Umm, all right here's the thing, for the last two weeks I have umm, tried really hard to create a positive atmosphere...

transcript: Can't hear you!

speaker: ['Monica Geller']
transcript: A positive atmosphere! But I-I-I have had it up to here. From now on, it is gonna be my way, or the highway! All right? Does anybody have a problem with that?!! Hey new guy! I said, does anybody have a problem with that?!

transcript: No ma'am.

transcript: Hey! He has a name, it's Dragon. Do you wanna know your name? Check your hat. We did the hat right?

transcript: What the hell happened?!

speaker: ['Joey Tribbiani']
transcript: I am so-so-so sorry. I was gonna do it! Really! But I was standing there with 327 dollars in one hand and 238 dollars in the other hand, and I was thinking, "Wow! It's been a long time since I had... 327 + 238 dollars!"

speaker: ['Monica Geller']
transcript: Joey, we had a deal. That-that's why you're here! I've got to fire you!

transcript: What kinda things have you been saying?

transcript: So! Ross doesn't really decorate his tree with floss, but you don't hear him complaining do you? God!

You take a train up to Poughkeepsie and break up with her, and on your way back you break up with uptown. And then by the time you get home tonight, you're done!
